Review_1: I have purchased it on 1st April 2015, I got delivery on 3rd April and same day installation. Installation cost is very high charged by whirlpool for installation. No options to reject the cost charged by whirlpool support engineer.Installation charges 1500/-Stand 850/-Vinyl tape insulator 250/-2 feet wire 50/-2 feet extra copper wire 500/- (Rs. 250/- per feet)Water Drainage pipe 400/-Total Installation cost 3450/-Due to High Installation cost, I have cancelled Vinyl tape insulator and Paid 3200/-While paying Rs 3200/- support engineer return me Rs. 100/- as bribe and told me to say whirlpool company that he charge me only Rs 2350/-So great product and branded company but poor support,I am not happy with installation. AC mounted not by fixing screws but they use hammering screw while fitting. One of my chair also get broken while installation as they do not have helper and there ladder. They do not have proper tools for installation.It was taken 5 PM to 11:30 PM for Installation by one man army installation engineerI suggest to buy AC with free installation charges.
Review_3: The product got delivered in 5 working days, which I think is fine.I need to pay the installation charges of INR1,500 and additional INR 1500 also for the extra Copper pipe at the rate of INR 750 per meter.I was  expecting the additional installation charges , as the same was mentioned in the terms and conditions at the time of purchase, however I was not expecting that I need to pay for the extra copper pipe and that's also for that much of high rate.The room size where I have installed the AC is 11ft x 10 ft and is not exposed to sun raise because of its direction, even though the cooling capacity of the AC is not that good.It took almost half an hour to cool the room at 6th sense and when I use the turbo mode it cools fast but..it becomes a bit humid. Its to be noted that my residence is not near sea side.Overall I find it to be okay, however find the price point very reasonable.
Review_2: DON'T BUY WHIRLPOOL AC.  My compressor stopped working, it was under warrantee.  When I called Whirlpool service center, they told me they will send a technician within 24 hours.  It's been 7 days now, recomplained again but never received any calls from their technician.  Obviously, they don't want to replace the compressor.  Finally, I've gotten fed up and sold my ac at dirt cheap price. Final Impression:  Short life span, 3rd class service, 3rd class product.
Review_4: Very good ac bought from store @32,400 cool my 10*11 room less than 10 minutes no word just amazing blindly trust brand whirlpool after all its made in u.s.a

I would recommend this AC for 24000 with free installation.

Review_1: I have been using this product (Qty 2) from last 3 years.  The best part is I can run at 500 watt 800 watt 1.1KWatt. The room size is 12x13 feet, middle floor (not directly exposed to sun from roof). Initially after installing , I had few issues with customer services (late service) but it got resolved.  Following drawback1) Remote control does not backlight2) There is no temperature display on the Dispense.Advantages1) Consumption of electricity is less,  reduction of electricity bill by 35-40% compare to window AC (Assembled).2)Silent4)Easy Maintenance.
Review_3: I have been using a Sharp inverter AC for more than 1 year and it is working well. When I decided to buy another one for children's room, I chose Sharp again since it looked a good product. However, the new inverter ac stopped working after a month. I raised a complaint and have been waiting for a resolution for more than 2 weeks now. I understand that Sharp does not have a solid process in place for customer support. They have outsourced the support functions to some small timers and you are at the mercy of these folks - they may or may not attend your complaint. I have called them at least 10 times. Warranty does not mean anything as the only thing Sharp does is give you a phone number of the outsourced support partner. As opposed to Sharp, Voltas and Daikin have a strong customer support process in place and hence my advise is to check the customer support availability at your location before you buy a Sharp product. I am from Cochin and the service here is pathetic.
Review_2: I have been using Sharp ac for more than 4 years.  During 1st year I was very happy with the performance.  But afterwards its performance became very poor.Only positive side= it's consumption of electricity.  Just half than any other non inverter 1.5 ton 5star AC.Cons= airflow is very very low.U will never feel chilling cold. Only a soothing coolness could be enjoyed.Customer service is very very poor.I will recommend you all to go for non inverter 5 star AC.
Review_4: Have been using this AC for 4 Months NowThe Cooling is Just BrilliantDue to the  Inverter Tech the bills are under control from 700Rs to 1300 RsUsage Pattern every day for 2-3 hrs and on weekends 14 hrs .However got the product from Vijay Sales in ThaneInstallation charges were 3000and i had to pay additional for Core Cutting the Wall ( Hole for the water pipe and cooling pipe to go thru so that the unit looks neat without wires hanging in your room)Its the only ac with I -odizer function and has a special function to remove moisture from the air in case your are drying clothes in the room)Overall great ac compared to anything out there.

Review_1: I have purchased it on 1st April 2015, I got delivery on 3rd April and same day installation. Installation cost is very high charged by whirlpool for installation. No options to reject the cost charged by whirlpool support engineer.Installation charges 1500/-Stand 850/-Vinyl tape insulator 250/-2 feet wire 50/-2 feet extra copper wire 500/- (Rs. 250/- per feet)Water Drainage pipe 400/-Total Installation cost 3450/-Due to High Installation cost, I have cancelled Vinyl tape insulator and Paid 3200/-While paying Rs 3200/- support engineer return me Rs. 100/- as bribe and told me to say whirlpool company that he charge me only Rs 2350/-So great product and branded company but poor support,I am not happy with installation. AC mounted not by fixing screws but they use hammering screw while fitting. One of my chair also get broken while installation as they do not have helper and there ladder. They do not have proper tools for installation.It was taken 5 PM to 11:30 PM for Installation by one man army installation engineerI suggest to buy AC with free installation charges.
Review_3: The product got delivered in 5 working days, which I think is fine.I need to pay the installation charges of INR1,500 and additional INR 1500 also for the extra Copper pipe at the rate of INR 750 per meter.I was  expecting the additional installation charges , as the same was mentioned in the terms and conditions at the time of purchase, however I was not expecting that I need to pay for the extra copper pipe and that's also for that much of high rate.The room size where I have installed the AC is 11ft x 10 ft and is not exposed to sun raise because of its direction, even though the cooling capacity of the AC is not that good.It took almost half an hour to cool the room at 6th sense and when I use the turbo mode it cools fast but..it becomes a bit humid. Its to be noted that my residence is not near sea side.Overall I find it to be okay, however find the price point very reasonable.
Review_2: DON'T BUY WHIRLPOOL AC.  My compressor stopped working, it was under warrantee.  When I called Whirlpool service center, they told me they will send a technician within 24 hours.  It's been 7 days now, recomplained again but never received any calls from their technician.  Obviously, they don't want to replace the compressor.  Finally, I've gotten fed up and sold my ac at dirt cheap price. Final Impression:  Short life span, 3rd class service, 3rd class product.

Review_3: I have been using a Sharp inverter AC for more than 1 year and it is working well. When I decided to buy another one for children's room, I chose Sharp again since it looked a good product. However, the new inverter ac stopped working after a month. I raised a complaint and have been waiting for a resolution for more than 2 weeks now. I understand that Sharp does not have a solid process in place for customer support. They have outsourced the support functions to some small timers and you are at the mercy of these folks - they may or may not attend your complaint. I have called them at least 10 times. Warranty does not mean anything as the only thing Sharp does is give you a phone number of the outsourced support partner. As opposed to Sharp, Voltas and Daikin have a strong customer support process in place and hence my advise is to check the customer support availability at your location before you buy a Sharp product. I am from Cochin and the service here is pathetic.

Review_1: I have purchased it on 1st April 2015, I got delivery on 3rd April and same day installation. Installation cost is very high charged by whirlpool for installation. No options to reject the cost charged by whirlpool support engineer.Installation charges 1500/-Stand 850/-Vinyl tape insulator 250/-2 feet wire 50/-2 feet extra copper wire 500/- (Rs. 250/- per feet)Water Drainage pipe 400/-Total Installation cost 3450/-Due to High Installation cost, I have cancelled Vinyl tape insulator and Paid 3200/-While paying Rs 3200/- support engineer return me Rs. 100/- as bribe and told me to say whirlpool company that he charge me only Rs 2350/-So great product and branded company but poor support,I am not happy with installation. AC mounted not by fixing screws but they use hammering screw while fitting. One of my chair also get broken while installation as they do not have helper and there ladder. They do not have proper tools for installation.It was taken 5 PM to 11:30 PM for Installation by one man army installation engineerI suggest to buy AC with free installation charges.
Review_3: The product got delivered in 5 working days, which I think is fine.I need to pay the installation charges of INR1,500 and additional INR 1500 also for the extra Copper pipe at the rate of INR 750 per meter.I was  expecting the additional installation charges , as the same was mentioned in the terms and conditions at the time of purchase, however I was not expecting that I need to pay for the extra copper pipe and that's also for that much of high rate.The room size where I have installed the AC is 11ft x 10 ft and is not exposed to sun raise because of its direction, even though the cooling capacity of the AC is not that good.It took almost half an hour to cool the room at 6th sense and when I use the turbo mode it cools fast but..it becomes a bit humid. Its to be noted that my residence is not near sea side.Overall I find it to be okay, however find the price point very reasonable.
Review_2: DON'T BUY WHIRLPOOL AC.  My compressor stopped working, it was under warrantee.  When I called Whirlpool service center, they told me they will send a technician within 24 hours.  It's been 7 days now, recomplained again but never received any calls from their technician.  Obviously, they don't want to replace the compressor.  Finally, I've gotten fed up and sold my ac at dirt cheap price. Final Impression:  Short life span, 3rd class service, 3rd class product.
Review_4: Very good ac bought from store @32,400 cool my 10*11 room less than 10 minutes no word just amazing blindly trust brand whirlpool after all its made in u.s.a
